### [John Chapter 14](../../../bib/kjv/joh014.htm#001.md)

[John 14:3](../../../bib/kjv/joh014.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">joh 14:3</span></span>

receive you unto myself

This promise of a second advent of Christ is to be distinguished from
His return in glory to the earth; it is the first intimation in
Scripture of "the day of Christ".

(See Scofield) - ([Co1 1:8](../../../bib/kjv/co1001.htm#008).md).

Here He comes for His saints ([Th1
4:14-17](../../../bib/kjv/th1004.htm#014).md); there ([Mat
24:29](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#029).md); ([Mat
24:30](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#030).md), He come to judge the nations,
etc.

[John 14:16](../../../bib/kjv/joh014.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">joh 14:16</span></span>

Comforter

Greek, "Parakletos", meaning "one called alongside to help." Translated
"advocate," ([Jo1 2:1](../../../bib/kjv/jo1002.htm#001).md). Christ is the
believer's Paraclete with the Father when he sins; the Holy Spirit the
believer's indwelling Paraclete to help his ignorance and infirmity and
to make intercession ([Rom 8:26](../../../bib/kjv/rom008.htm#026).md);
([Rom 8:27](../../../bib/kjv/rom008.htm#027).md).

(See "Holy Spirit," New Testament doctrine,) ([Mat
1:18](../../../bib/kjv/mat001.htm#018).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Act 2:4](../../../bib/kjv/act002.htm#004).md).

And I will

(See Scofield) - ([Luk 11:13](../../../bib/kjv/luk011.htm#013).md).

